## Error Handling

### Safe Error Messages

Errors returned to users:
- Include error type and code
- Provide helpful guidance
- Do NOT include stack traces
- Do NOT include secrets or internal paths

### Example

```typescript
// Good
return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Error: Invalid API response' }], isError: true };

// Bad (don't do this)
return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: `Error: ${error.stack}` }], isError: true };
```

